A function as a block of code with a name that performs a service. 

When a function is located inside a class, it is called a method. 

package JavaHello;

/** This is an implementation of the traditional "Hello world!" message
 * 
 * @author KaiserinDerWelt
 *
 */
public class HelloWorld {
	
	/** This is where the program starts */ /*Main Function*/
	public static void main(String[] args) {
		System.out.println("Hello World!");
	}

}
